explanation: The solution iteratively clears the rightmost set bit in the binary representation of n. It uses bitwise operations for efficiency. Clearing a single bit takes constant time, and the loop iterates until all bits are cleared, resulting in a logarithmic time complexity.  The algorithm uses a constant amount of extra space.

